description:
This is a 6 minute workout called '5 Minute Morning Yoga - Daily Stretching Routine' from the channel Yoga with Kassandra.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Yoga and Flexibility/Stretching.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Zen Flow and The Reboot Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Short on time but need a good stretch? Enjoy this quick 5 minute morning yoga flow.

Hey everyone, this morning I'm going to take you through a quick and simple yoga sequence to energize and stretch your body. I know 5 minutes isn't a lot of time but trust me, you'll feel better by the end of it!

We'll begin standing up with a side bend sequence to energize your body before going into poses like ragdoll, temple pose, wide legged forward fold and  downward facing dog. A little bit of yoga is better than none, so let's get to it :) No props needed and suitable for all levels.
